  "text": "The ConfigMap and Secret immutability feature in Kubernetes is implemented across multiple files in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0. The feature consists of three key components:\n\n1. **Immutable Field Definition**: The Immutable field is defined in both the public API types (staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go at lines 7540 for ConfigMap and 7397 for Secret) and the internal types (pkg/apis/core/types.go at lines 6281 for ConfigMap and 6153 for Secret). This field is a pointer to bool that indicates whether the data in the ConfigMap or Secret can be modified.\n\n2. **Immutable Field Validation and Mutation Prevention**: The validation logic is implemented in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go. The ValidateConfigMapUpdate function (lines 6898-6912) and ValidateSecretUpdate function (lines 6841-6858) check if the old object has Immutable set to true. If it does, they prevent modifications to the Data/BinaryData fields and prevent unsetting the Immutable field. These functions also call ValidateImmutableField (line 363) to validate the Type field for Secrets. The validation functions are used by the strategy implementations in pkg/registry/core/configmap/strategy.go (line 87) and pkg/registry/core/secret/strategy.go (line 89) during REST API updates.\n\n3. **Watch Optimization**: The watch optimization that skips immutable objects is implemented in pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager.go. The objectCacheItem struct (lines 46-64) contains an immutable boolean field and methods to set it (setImmutable at lines 90-94). When an object is retrieved through GetObject (lines 333-348), if it is detected to be immutable via the isImmutable callback function, the reflector watch is stopped by calling item.stop(), preventing unnecessary watch events for immutable objects. The restartReflectorIfNeeded method (lines 109-118) checks the immutable flag and skips restarting the reflector if the object is immutable. The isImmutable callback functions are defined in pkg/kubelet/configmap/configmap_manager.go (lines 148-153) for ConfigMaps and pkg/kubelet/secret/secret_manager.go (lines 149-154) for Secrets. These implementations are used by NewWatchingConfigMapManager (line 138) and NewWatchingSecretManager (line 139) to create watch-based managers that optimize resource usage by stopping watches on immutable objects."
}

